msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p> 
#. VAR: Ovādavagga → nāvābhirū­hana­sikkhā­padaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 28"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:0.5"
msgid "28. Nāvābhiruhanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on boarding boats"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-pc28.1, pts-vp-en.2.292, ms2V_609
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#. VAR: ekaṃ nāvaṃ → ekanāvaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhanti."
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six boarded a boat by appointment with nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized them,"

#. VAR: nāvāya → ekanāvāya (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.4"
msgid "“yatheva mayaṃ sapajāpatikā nāvāya kīḷāma, evamevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya nāvāya kīḷantī”ti."
msgstr "“Just as we amuse ourselves on boats with our wives, so these Sakyan ascetics make appointments with nuns and then amuse themselves on boats.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_610
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.5"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.6"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.7"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six board boats by appointments with nuns?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.9"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.11"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.12"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you board boats by appointments with nuns?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.13"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.14"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. HTML: </h3><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: ekaṃ nāvaṃ → ekanāvaṃ (s1-3)
#. REF: sc3,  ms2V_611,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.15"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruheyya, uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk boards a boat by appointment with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p class="endsection">
#. REF: sc4, ms2V_612
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:1.16"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli4.65, pts-cs-bu-pc28.2, ms2V_613
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca sāketā sāvatthiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti."
msgstr "Soon afterwards a number of monks and nuns were traveling from Sāketa to Sāvatthī."

#. VAR: taritabbā → uttaritabbā (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.2"
msgid "Antarāmagge nadī taritabbā hoti."
msgstr "On the way they had to cross a river,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and the nuns said to the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.4"
msgid "“mayampi ayyehi saddhiṃ uttarissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“We’ll cross with you.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en.2.293
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.5"
msgid "“Na, bhaginī, kappati bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhituṃ;"
msgstr "“Sisters, it’s not allowable for us to board a boat by appointment with a nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.6"
msgid "tumhe vā paṭhamaṃ uttaratha mayaṃ vā uttarissāmā”ti."
msgstr "You should cross first, or we will.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.7"
msgid "“Ayyā, bhante, aggapurisā."
msgstr "“Venerables, you have the highest status."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.8"
msgid "Ayyāva paṭhamaṃ uttarantū”ti."
msgstr "Please go first.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.9"
msgid "Atha kho tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ pacchā uttarantīnaṃ corā acchindiṃsu ca dūsesuñca."
msgstr "But because the nuns crossed afterwards, they were robbed and raped by bandits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.10"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "When they arrived at Sāvatthī they told the nuns there what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.11"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The nuns then told the monks,"

#. REF: ms2V_614
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.12"
msgid "Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "who in turn told the Master."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.13"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.14"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tiriyaṃ taraṇāya bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhituṃ."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to board a boat by appointment with a nun if it’s for the purpose of crossing."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.15"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "”And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: uddhaṅgāminiṃ → uddhagāminiṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: tiriyaṃ taraṇāya → tiri­yantara­ṇāya (s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: ekaṃ nāvaṃ → ekanāvaṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: abhiruheyya → abhirūheyya (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. REF: sc7, ms2V_615
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:2.16"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruheyya uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk boards a boat by appointment with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, unless it is for the purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, pts-cs-bu-pc28.3.1, ms2V_616
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… he monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms2V_617
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "A nun:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.7"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "she has been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_618
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.8"
msgid "Saddhinti"
msgstr "With:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.9"
msgid "ekato."
msgstr "together."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms2V_619
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.10"
msgid "Saṃvidhāyāti"
msgstr "By appointment:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.11"
msgid "“abhiruhāma, bhagini, abhiruhāmāyya; abhiruhāmāyya, abhiruhāma, bhagini; ajja vā hiyyo vā pare vā abhiruhāmā”ti saṃvidahati āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "if he makes an appointment like this: he says, “Let’s board, Sister,” and she replies, “Yes, let’s board, Venerable;” or she says, “Lets’s board, Venerable,” and he replies, “Yes, let’s board, Sister;” or he says, “Let’s board today/tomorrow/the day after tomorrow,” then he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms2V_620
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.12"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyā abhiruḷhe bhikkhu abhiruhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the monk boards when the nun has already boarded, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.13"
msgid "Bhikkhumhi abhiruḷhe bhikkhunī abhiruhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If the nun boards when the monks has already boarded, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.14"
msgid "Ubho vā abhiruhanti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If they both board together, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms2V_621
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.15"
msgid "Uddhaṅgāmininti"
msgstr "To go upstream:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.16"
msgid "ujjavanikāya."
msgstr "for the purpose of going against the stream."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc14, pts-vp-en.2.294, ms2V_622
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.17"
msgid "Adhogāmininti"
msgstr "To go downstream:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. REF: ms2V_623
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.18"
msgid "ojavanikāya."
msgstr "for the purpose of going with the stream."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.19"
msgid "Aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāyāti"
msgstr "Unless it is for the purpose of crossing:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.20"
msgid "ṭhapetvā tiriyaṃ taraṇaṃ."
msgstr "except to go across."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc16, ms2V_624
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.21"
msgid "Kukkuṭasampāte gāme, gāmantare gāmantare āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "When the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every village interval he commits an offense entailing confession."

# NOTE: Half a _yojana_. The length of a _yojana_ is uncertain, and perhaps it never was a precise distance. But a reasonable estimate is 8 miles or just under 13 kilometers (see ACMC, p.16). Thus half a _yojana_ is just over 6 km.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.1.22"
msgid "Agāmake araññe, aḍḍhayojane aḍḍhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is in an uninhabited area, in the wilderness, then for every six kilometers he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc17, pts-vp-pli4.66, pts-cs-bu-pc28.3.2, ms2V_625
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.2.1"
msgid "Saṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhati uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If there is an appointment, and he perceives that there is, and he boards a boat with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, unless it is for the purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.2.2"
msgid "Saṃvidahite vematiko ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhati uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If there is an appointment, but he is unsure if there is, and he boards a boat with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, unless it is for the purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.2.3"
msgid "Saṃvidahite asaṃvidahitasaññī ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhati uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If there is an appointment, but he perceives that there is not, and he boards a boat with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, unless it is for the purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18, ms2V_626
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.2.4"
msgid "Bhikkhu saṃvidahati, bhikkhunī na saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the monk makes an appointment, but the nun does not express her agreement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.2.5"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If there is no appointment, but he perceives that there is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.2.6"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If there is no appointment, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.2.7"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite, asaṃvidahitasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If there is no appointment, and he perceives that there is not, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc19, pts-cs-bu-pc28.3.3, ms2V_627
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.3.2"
msgid "tiriyaṃ taraṇāya,"
msgstr "if it is for the purpose of crossing;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.3.3"
msgid "asaṃvidahitvā abhiruhanti,"
msgstr "if he boards without an appointment;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.3.4"
msgid "bhikkhunī saṃvidahati, bhikkhu na saṃvidahati,"
msgstr "if the nun has made an appointment, but he has not expressed his agreement;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.3.5"
msgid "visaṅketena abhiruhanti,"
msgstr "if they board, but not according to the appointment;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.3.6"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.3.8"
msgid "ādikammissāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc20, ms2V_628
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc28:3.3.9"
msgid "Nāvābhiruhanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The eighth rule, the training rule on boarding boats, is finished."
